replies.body:
7: dark harvest is like thresh souls. You collect them and the count never resets.

For example you could be at 10 stacks and not have the proc available in lane, then the enemy cannon minion dies and drops a soul. You collect this soul (which brings your total to 15 because cannon minion souls are worth 5 stacks) which activate the buff for 20 seconds. Now you auto you lane opponent and consume the proc but keep your stacks. A few more hits and you kill the opponent and the drop a soul. You collect their soul and get stacks (I believe it is 10 for champ souls?) Raising your total (to 25?) And reactivation the buff for 20 seconds. If the buff runs out of time and you do not auto a champ or structure, you still keep the same soul count.

It is one of the many new uncapped scaling runes.{{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
